      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The correlation you see is a direct result of the economic incentives created by those benefits. When the reward for *not* working is substantially higher than the reward for taking a low-wage job, the choice to remain outside the labor market becomes rational for many. Therefore, the \"generosity\" itself is the mechanism driving the disincentive, making the design flaw rooted in the level of support provided.",
      "source": "target",
